column1: # Protein 1: UniProt accession of the first protein
# Protein 2: UniProt accession of the second protein
# Name 1: UniProt gene name of the first protein
# Name 2: UniProt gene name of the second protein
# AFprob5: the maximal AF2 interaction probability among five additional models we generated
# AFMprob: the maximal AFmm interaction probability among the five additional models we generated

# Source: indicate the pair is predicted based on which pipeline among those shown in Fig. 3A. D: de novo screening among protein pairs that share subcellular locality; U: de novo screening among protein pairs involving proteins without known subcellular locality; S: screening among genetically associated pairs extracted from the STRING database; P: screening among protein pairs from PPI databases (UniProt, BioGrid, and STRING physical interactions)

# PDBtemp: whether this pair has templates in PDB. Exact: the exact protein pair has determined structures in PDB; ortholog: with orthologous (identity > 50% for both proteins) templates in PDB; homolog: with homologous (detectable by MMseqs, e-value < 0.00001) templates in PDB; none: no templates

# confDBs: databases where this PPI is considered confident. STRING: with physical interaction combined score above 700; UniProt: all the interactions in UniProt (which has a relatively small number of PPIs); BioGriD: belonging to the Multi-Validated (MV) set
# allDBs: databases where this PPI is present
# STRING: total genetic interaction score from STRING
# Known1: how well-characterized the first protein is, based on Unknome database; a lower score means poorly characterized
# Known2: how well-characterized the second protein is, based on Unknome database; a lower score means poorly characterized
# Count1: number of linked PubMed papers to the first protein
# Count2: number of linked PubMed papers to the second protein
# Locality1: UniProt keywords in the cellular component category associated with the first protein
# Locality2: UniProt keywords in the cellular component category associated with the second protein
# Disease1: associated diseases for the first protein according to UniProt
# Disease2: associated diseases for the second protein according to UniProt
# Process1: UniProt keywords in the biological process category associated with the first protein
# Process2: UniProt keywords in the biological process category associated with the second protein
# Function1: UniProt protein name (function annotation) for the first protein
# Function2: UniProt protein name (function annotation) for the second protein
# Exact_templates: list of PDB IDs containing the exact protein pair
# Ortho_templates: list of PDB IDs containing interacting chain pairs that can serve as orthologous (identity > 50%) templates for the predicted PPI
# Homo_templates: list of PDB IDs containing interacting chain pairs that can serve as homologous (MMseqs e-value < 0.00001) templates for the predicted PPI
